title: Champs-Elysées
overview: Champs-Élysées was a French television variety show presented by Michel Drucker and broadcast live from January 9, 1982 to June 1985 and from January 1986 to June 29, 1990 every Saturday evening on Antenne 2, for around 300 episodes, and irregularly on France 2 from November 13, 2010 to May 11, 2013. The show owes its name to the fact that it is broadcast live from the Pavillon Gabriel, located on Avenue Gabriel along the Champs-Élysées in Paris.
